<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1349,1736]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">
Etymology: The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Handal, Al-Shaheen, Al-Saedy &amp; Wulff" authorityYear="2022" box="[487,583,1421,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Fallacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fawensis">
<emphasis box="[487,583,1421,1447]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">fawensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the Faw town in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1095,1422,1448]" name="Iraq" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Iraq</collectingCountry>
where this species was first encountered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="75" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1349,1736]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">
Ecology: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Handal, Al-Shaheen, Al-Saedy &amp; Wulff" authorityYear="2022" box="[298,495,1493,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Fallacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fawensis">
<emphasis box="[298,495,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Fallacia fawensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a rare epipelic species within the diatom community found on the muddy shores of Shatt Al–Arab River at Faw town, Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[691,740,1530,1556]" name="Iraq" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. Salinity at time of collection was 5.2 and water temperature 38°C. On all slides prepared from the samples, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Handal, Al-Shaheen, Al-Saedy &amp; Wulff" authorityYear="2022" box="[675,799,1565,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Fallacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fawensis">
<emphasis box="[675,799,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">F. fawensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constituted an average of 1.2% of the other taxa and was associated with some common taxa including 
<taxonomicName authority="(Giffen) Witkowski, Lange" authorityName="Witkowski, Lange" baseAuthorityName="Giffen" box="[645,1201,1601,1628]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Entomoneidaceae" genus="Entomoneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Surirellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="corrugata">
<emphasis box="[645,895,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Entomoneis corrugata</emphasis>
(Giffen) Witkowski, Lange
</taxonomicName>
–Bertalot &amp; Metzelten (2000:198)(3.75%), 
<taxonomicName box="[365,546,1637,1664]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Amphipleuraceae" genus="Halamphora" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[365,508,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Halamphora</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(4.5%), 
<taxonomicName authority="Hanitzsch (1860: 40)" authorityName="Hanitzsch" authorityPageNumber="40" authorityYear="1860" box="[642,1068,1637,1663]" class="Monogenea" family="Capsalidae" genus="Nitzschia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Capsalidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="clausii">
<emphasis box="[642,827,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Nitzschia clausii</emphasis>
Hanitzsch (1860: 40)
</taxonomicName>
(7.3 %), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kutzing) W. Smith (1856: 89)" authorityName="W. Smith" authorityPageNumber="89" authorityYear="1856" baseAuthorityName="Kutzing" class="Monogenea" family="Capsalidae" genus="Nitzschia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Capsalidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="palea">
<emphasis box="[1164,1336,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Nitzschia palea</emphasis>
(Kützing) W. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, W." box="[166,355,1673,1700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5123" refString="Smith, W. (1856) A synopsis of the British Diatomaceae; with remarks on their structure, functions and distribution; and instructions for collecting and preserving specimens. Vol. 2. A-E. John van Voorst., London, pp. 1 - 107." type="book" year="1856">Smith (1856:89)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(9.5%) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ehrenberg) D. G. Mann" authorityName="D. G. Mann" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" box="[506,1019,1673,1700]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Surirellaceae" genus="Petrodictyon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Surirellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="gemma">
<emphasis box="[506,742,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Petrodictyon gemma</emphasis>
(Ehrenberg) D.G.Mann
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Round, F. E. &amp; Crawford, R. M. &amp; Mann, D. G." box="[1073,1348,1673,1700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5019" refString="Round, F. E., Crawford, R. M. &amp; Mann, D. G. (1990) The diatoms, Biology and Morphology of the Genera. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge." type="book" year="1990">
Round 
<emphasis box="[1158,1219,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
1990:638
</bibRefCitation>
) (7.5%). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Handal, Al-Shaheen, Al-Saedy &amp; Wulff" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,334,1709,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Fallacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fawensis">
<emphasis box="[136,334,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Fallacia fawensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not encountered in samples collected from northern parts of Shatt Al–Arab River.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
